MUT workflow release cut --version <semver>
🧭 Runtime COT | id=<id+1> | what=release stabilization | action=start release stabilization | why=create the ticket-scoped stabilization work from the frozen release line | command=MUT workflow release stabilize --release release/<semver> --kind <kind> --key <KEY> --ticket <NUMBER> --slug <slug> | status=about-to-run
MUT workflow release stabilize --release release/<semver> --kind <kind> --key <KEY> --ticket <NUMBER> --slug <slug>
🧭 Runtime COT | id=<id+2> | what=release stabilization publication | action=publish the stabilization branch and create its pull request | why=submit the verified release-only change for review | command=GH workflow release publish-stabilization --release release/<semver> --push --create-pull-request | status=about-to-run
GH workflow release publish-stabilization --release release/<semver> --push --create-pull-request
🧭 Runtime COT | id=<id+3> | what=release promotion | action=create the release-to-main pull request | why=promote the approved release through review without directly mutating main | command=GH workflow release promote --release release/<semver> --create-pull-request | status=about-to-run
GH workflow release promote --release release/<semver> --create-pull-request
🧭 Runtime COT | id=<id+4> | what=release backmerge | action=create the release-to-develop pull request | why=return approved release changes to the integration line through review | command=GH workflow release backmerge --release release/<semver> --create-pull-request | status=about-to-run
GH workflow release backmerge --release release/<semver> --create-pull-request
